\end_inset

.
 The stress function has the following features:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The stress is a periodic function, with the stress repeating every time
 the displacement is increased by an amount equal to 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

, the distance between atoms along the slip direction.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The stress is equal to zero at the stable equilibrium positions at 
\begin_inset Formula $u=0,\,b,\,2b$
\end_inset

, etc.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
For 
\begin_inset Formula $u<b/2$
\end_inset

