 out of their stable equilibrium positions.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
At 
\begin_inset Formula $u=b/2$
\end_inset

 the system is at an unstable equilibrium.
 The stress is also equal to zero at this position, but the equilibrium
 is unstable because any slight perturbation in the displacement will cause
 the atomic plane to fall back into an equilibrium position at 
\begin_inset Formula $u=0$
\end_inset

 or 
\begin_inset Formula $u=b$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The maximum stress is at 
\begin_inset Formula $u=b/4$
\end_inset

 .
 The stress actually reverses sign for 
\begin_inset Formula $u>b/2$
\end_inset

, since a stress must be applied to avoid having the atoms fall into the
