 What is really going on here? The answer is that slip occurs by the motion
 of dislocations, not by the concerted motion of entire planes of atoms
 across one another.
 The concept of slip by dislocation motion can be illustrated conceptually
 by the force required to slide a carpet across a floor.
 If the friction between the rug and the floor is very high, it's going
