 If the rug just needs to be moved a small distance it is much easier to
 create a wrinkle at one end of the rug and move it to the other end of
 the carpet.
 At the end of the process, the carpet has moved by a length equal to the
 length of extra carpet stored in the wrinkle.
 Dislocations are line defects in crystalline materials that are analogous
 to these wrinkles.
 
