\begin_inset Formula $\vec{n}_{d}$
\end_inset

 has the following properties:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Because redefining 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{s}$
\end_inset

 to have the opposite orientation also changes the orientation of 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{b}$
\end_inset

, the negative signs cancel and we end up with a value for 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{n}_{d}$
\end_inset

 that is independent of the way that we choose to define 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{s}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
For a pure screw dislocation, 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta=0$
\end_inset

 or 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta=180^{\circ}$
\end_inset

