\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This last point is perhaps the most important one, because it provides an
 easy way to figure out how the extra half plane is oriented in an edge
 dislocation, once we specify the orientations of 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{b}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{s}$
\end_inset

.
 We just use the right hand rule, cross 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{b}$
\end_inset

