\begin_layout Standard
With our convention for using the Burgers circuit to obtain 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{b}$
\end_inset

 (Right-hand-rule, start to finish), we have the following relationships
 between 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{s}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{b}$
\end_inset

:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Right-handed screw dislocation: 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{s}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{b}$
\end_inset

 point in opposite directions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Left-handed screw dislocation: 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{s}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{b}$
\end_inset

 point in the same direction.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Edge dislocation: 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{s}$
\end_inset

 perpendicular to 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{b}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{b}\times\hat{s}$
\end_inset

 points to the extra half plane.
\end_layout

