\begin_layout Standard
How does the melting point of a pure material depend on its size? We'll
 assume that the solid material has a radius of 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

, and that the solid/liquid interfacial free energy is 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma$
\end_inset

.
 As illustrated schematically in Figure 
