\begin_layout Subsubsection
Grain Boundary Junctions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In this case the three phase contact line is actually a junction between
 grain boundaries, as opposed to a place where three distinct phases come
 into contact with one another.
 The important points are the following:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If the three grain boundary energies for the boundaries meeting at the contact
 line are all equal to one another, 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{1}=\theta_{2}=60^{\circ}$
\end_inset

.
 In other words, the interior angles between the different grains are all
 120
\begin_inset Formula $^{\circ}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
As a corollary to the point above, the boundaries of grains with fewer than
 6 sides will be curved outward and the grain will tend to shrink, whereas
 grains with more than 6 sides will have boundaries that are curved and
 the grains will tend to grow.
\end_layout

